    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Hierarchical Service Function Chaining (hSFC) is a network architecture allowing an organization to decompose a large-scale network into multiple domains of administration.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The goals of hSFC are to make a large-scale network easier to design, simpler to control, and supportive of independent functional groups within large network operators.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
